history.text: So we are going to talk about the movie The Wolf of Wall Street
Yes, it seems to have gotten mixed audience reviews.
Yes, apparently some critics found the characters dull!
I find it interesting that even though the critical response seems to be negative, it still managed to get a 78% on Rotten Tomatoes.

Dull characters in a black comedy do not sound appealing!
I can understand the average scoring
I think the quality of the actors probably helped
You have DiCaprio, Margot Robbie and Jonah Hill
Also being directed by Scorsese is a plus.
No kidding
The story sounds good on paper but it doesn't appear like it translated well to the screen.
The supporting cast is pretty good too, with Jon Favreau and Matthew McConaughey
It sure seems that way.  It was based on a memoir, so I guess you can only go so far in making it interesting if it wasn't before!
Exactly, big names only go so far.
It looks like the main character was a stock broker.  That does seem like it could be a little cliched.  The summary mentions corruption and drugs, and that story may get old!
Sex, drugs, and money. It had been done before.
It sure has!
It had potential with the main character going from a small fish in a big pond to a big fish in a small pond early in his career, but I guess the movie took a turn after that.
Greed is not always fun to watch I guess!
It can come off as kind of one note.
A lot of the audience may not remember that 80s finance party culture either
Wow, that latest bit of the summary makes the movie seem hard to follow.  A lot going on there!
Yeah, it looks like if you don't have basic knowledge of finances it could be hard to watch.
Sex, drugs and money seem like such a good combination....  until you need to think too.  LOL.
Haha, it looks like they were trying to make three different movies in one and it got too complicated along the way.
yes, I understand now why the critics said it was epic in size and claustrophobic in scope.  They seem to have tried to cover an entire complicated life in a couple of hours
I wonder what the actual running time of the movie was, I'd have to imagine it would be pretty long.
Well that took a turn at the end!
He lost his mind and stole his daughter.
And then worked with and against the FBI at the same time.
and somehow managed to break his agreement, only spend three years in a country club prison and then still make a living giving seminars
I'm not sure how I feel about this ending. And he obviously got paid for optioning his autobiography into a film. I would feel a little sour if I just watched this!
That ending isn't really satisfying at all, I would understand if that was why critics didn't exactly love it.

Yeah, even if there were good portions the wrap up just seems very unsatisfying.  The main character seems like a real jerk and three years in prison does not make me feel like he got what he had coming.
Like you're not exactly rooting for this guy, and then he gets a happy ending.

uid1response.feedback: I found it kind of hard to only use the information in the document as this was a movie I had seen MULTIPLE times and have very strong opinions on.
